Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace PR14f-prep ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) stubs with real silicon-resident
source-TD + member-AD MURAM allocation per LS1046A RM 8.7.7 (Frame
replicator group table format).

- struct fman_pcd_replic_group (private to TU): list anchor on
  pcd->replic_groups, pcd back-pointer, num_members, source_td/members
  MURAM off+iomem, members_sz, spinlock for body-3 runtime updates.
- create() validates args (pcd, members, num_members in [1,64]),
  allocates source-TD (16 B) + members array (num_members*16 B) via
  fman_pcd_muram_alloc(), memset_io zero both regions, stamps the
  source-TD type field with FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE (0x75),
  list_add_tail on pcd->replic_groups under pcd->lock.
- destroy() is exact reverse: list_del under lock, zero before free,
  fman_pcd_muram_free() in reverse order, kfree handle.
- Pre-declares body-2 constants (FR_BIT, NL_BIT, ADDR_SHIFT,
  INVALID_MEMBER_INDEX) and source-TD record offsets per RM Table 8-128.

Body-1 deliberately does NOT consume the members[] arg yet — FQID
encoding + NEXT chaining + NL_BIT stamping lands in body-2 as one
atomic programming pass.  All-zero MURAM keeps silicon walker
inactive (operationCode=0 short-circuits the walker), preserving the
same inactive-state safety invariant as PR14d-body-1 (HMCT all-zero)
and PR14e-body-1 (PLCR record all-zero).
---
 .../ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_replic.c | 305 +++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 266 insertions(+), 39 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_replic.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_replic.c
index 3482b2019..9d46bef39 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_replic.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_replic.c
@@ -1,83 +1,310 @@
 // SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
 /*
- * FMan PCD Frame Replicator - public API stubs.
+ * FMan PCD Frame Replicator - real MURAM bodies (PR14f-body-1).
  *
- * PR14f-prep of the ASK2 v1.0 PR14 series (replicator half).  Declares
- * the on-disk translation unit for the multicast-fanout layer and
- * provides ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) / no-op stubs for every public entry
- * point declared in <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>.  PR14f-body replaces these
- * stubs with the real silicon-programming code per LS1046A RM 8.7.7
+ * Replaces the PR14f-prep ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) stubs in
+ * fman_pcd_replic_group_create() / _destroy() with real silicon-resident
+ * source-TD + member-AD MURAM allocation per LS1046A RM 8.7.7
  * (Frame replicator group table format).
  *
  * Authoritative reference
  * -----------------------
- * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.7 (Frame replicator).
+ * - LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.7 (Frame replicator) - silicon-fact
+ *   source of the source-TD record layout, member-AD chaining via
+ *   NEXT_FRM_REPLIC_ADDR_SHIFT, FR/NL bits, and the 64-member hard limit.
  *
  * Provenance (v1.1)
  * ---------------------
  * Mainline drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/ has zero replicator
  * code; this file is authored from the RM only.  The legacy NXP SDK
- * fm_replic.c (~900 LOC under drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/
- * Peripherals/FM/Pcd/ in the archived mihakralj/kernel-ls1046a-build
- * repo at HEAD 464df181) is a read-only silicon-fact cross-reference
- * only - no code or struct layouts are copied from it.  See spec
- * specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 16 (provenance discipline risk #12).
+ * fm_replic.c / fm_replic.h under drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/
+ * sdk_fman/Peripherals/FM/Pcd/ in the archived
+ * mihakralj/kernel-ls1046a-build repo at HEAD 464df181 is a read-only
+ * silicon-fact cross-reference only - no code or struct layouts are
+ * copied.  See spec specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 16 (provenance
+ * discipline risk #12).
  *
- * What this file delivers at PR14f-prep
- * -------------------------------------
- * Two public entry points, both returning ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) /
- * no-op.  No struct fman_pcd_replic_group definition yet - it stays
- * forward-declared in <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>.  No MURAM allocation,
- * no register writes.  PR14f-body materialises the silicon-resident
- * replicator-group table.  Consumed in M3 by IPv4 / IPv6 multicast
- * flow types (OP_FLOW_INSERT_V4_MCAST / _V6_MCAST per spec sec 12).
+ * Body-1 scope
+ * ------------
+ * - struct fman_pcd_replic_group (private to TU): list anchor on
+ *   pcd->replic_groups, pcd back-pointer, cached num_members, source-TD
+ *   MURAM offset+iomem, members-array MURAM offset+iomem, members-array
+ *   byte size, spinlock_t lock for body-3 add/remove softirq paths.
+ * - Real create() validates args, allocates source-TD (16 B) +
+ *   members array (num_members * 16 B), memset_io zero (all-zero source-TD
+ *   has operationCode=0 = inactive; silicon walker never invoked even
+ *   when no NL_BIT marks the members), populates source-TD type field
+ *   with FRM_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE so it is recognised as a replicator
+ *   anchor when activated by body-3.  Note: body-1 deliberately does
+ *   NOT chain the members via their NEXT pointers nor stamp NL_BIT -
+ *   body-2 (member-AD encoder) does that as a single atomic
+ *   programming pass.
+ * - Real destroy() is the exact reverse: list_del under pcd->lock,
+ *   free members array, free source-TD, kfree handle.
+ *
+ * Body-2 will add the member-AD encoder (FQID into each 16-B member
+ * slot, NEXT pointer chaining via FRM_REPLIC_ADDR_SHIFT, NL_BIT on the
+ * last member, FR_BIT to enable per-member fan-out) and stamp them in
+ * one pass under group->lock so silicon never sees a partial chain.
+ * Body-3 wires cc_encode_ad() FMAN_PCD_ACTION_REPLICATE to point AD.res
+ * at group->source_td_off.  Body-4 lands the KUnit suite covering the
+ * source-TD layout byte-perfect against RM 8.7.7 and the member-AD
+ * chaining math.
  */
 
 #include <linux/err.h>
 #include <linux/errno.h>
 #include <linux/export.h>
+#include <linux/io.h>
 #include <linux/kernel.h>
+#include <linux/list.h>
 #include <linux/module.h>
+#include <linux/mutex.h>
+#include <linux/slab.h>
+#include <linux/spinlock.h>
 #include <linux/types.h>
 
 #include <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>
+#include "fman.h"
+#include "fman_muram.h"
 #include "fman_pcd_internal.h"
 
-/* Silicon hard limit per RM 8.7.7: 64 members per replicator group. */
-#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_MAX_MEMBERS 64
+/*
+ * Silicon hard limit per LS1046A RM sec 8.7.7: a single replicator group
+ * may hold up to 64 members.  Matches the SDK FM_PCD_MAX_NUM_OF_REPLIC_MEMBERS
+ * value (cross-ref read-only) and is exposed in the public header doc.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_MAX_MEMBERS		64
+
+/*
+ * Source-TD record is 16 B per RM sec 8.7.7 (cross-ref SDK fm_replic.h
+ * t_FrmReplicGroupSourceAd, which is 4 x u32).  Member-AD records are
+ * also 16 B each - same layout as CC ADs (fqid/plcr/nia/res) with the
+ * NEXT_FRM_REPLIC_ADDR_SHIFT field packed into the NIA word.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE			16
+
+/*
+ * Body-2 register constants pre-declared in body-1 so the encoder drop
+ * lands with zero new constants.  Per RM sec 8.7.7 + cross-ref SDK
+ * fm_replic.h lines 46-55:
+ *
+ *   - SOURCE_TD_OPCODE 0x75: stamped into the source-TD type field; the
+ *     silicon parser-classifier walker recognises this as the entry
+ *     point of a replicator chain.
+ *   - FR_BIT 0x08000000: NIA[27] - "Fan-out enable" on each member AD.
+ *   - NL_BIT 0x10000000: NIA[28] - "No-Link" terminates the chain;
+ *     stamped into the LAST member's NIA word.
+ *   - ADDR_SHIFT 4: NEXT pointer is the high-order MURAM offset
+ *     of the next member, shifted left 4 (i.e. 16-B aligned).
+ *   - INVALID_MEMBER_INDEX 0xffff: sentinel for body-2 "no successor"
+ *     while still inside the chain (only the LAST member has NL_BIT
+ *     set; intermediate vacant slots use this sentinel).
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE	0x75u
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_FR_BIT			0x08000000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_NL_BIT			0x10000000u
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_ADDR_SHIFT		4
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_INVALID_MEMBER_INDEX	0xffffu
+
+/* Source-TD record offsets (RM sec 8.7.7 Table 8-128). */
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SRC_OFF_TYPE		0x0
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SRC_OFF_FRG_POINTER	0x4
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SRC_OFF_OPCODE		0x8
+#define FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SRC_OFF_RES		0xc
+
+/**
+ * struct fman_pcd_replic_group - one MURAM-resident replicator group.
+ * @node: anchor on pcd->replic_groups
+ * @pcd: parent PCD context (back-pointer)
+ * @num_members: 1..FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_MAX_MEMBERS
+ * @source_td_off: MURAM byte offset of the source-TD record (16 B)
+ * @source_td: iomem pointer of the source-TD record
+ * @members_off: MURAM byte offset of the members-array (num_members * 16 B)
+ * @members: iomem pointer of the members-array base
+ * @members_sz: byte size of the members array (cached for free)
+ * @lock: serialises body-3 add/remove paths against runtime updates
+ *
+ * Body-1 keeps the struct private to fman_pcd_replic.c.  Body-3 will
+ * expose a cross-TU accessor (mirror of fman_pcd_manip_hmtd_off()) so
+ * cc_encode_ad() can read source_td_off when encoding the REPLICATE
+ * arm without depending on the layout.
+ */
+struct fman_pcd_replic_group {
+	struct list_head	node;
+	struct fman_pcd		*pcd;
+	u8			num_members;
+	unsigned long		source_td_off;
+	void __iomem		*source_td;
+	unsigned long		members_off;
+	void __iomem		*members;
+	size_t			members_sz;
+	spinlock_t		lock;
+};
 
 /**
  * fman_pcd_replic_group_create() - allocate a replicator group.
  *
- * PR14f-prep stub.  See <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h> for the full contract.
- * Returns ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) until PR14f-body lands.
+ * Body-1 real allocation.  See <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h> for the contract.
+ *
+ * Sequence:
+ *   1. arg validate (pcd, members, num_members in [1, 64])
+ *   2. kzalloc handle, init lock + list node, cache num_members + pcd
+ *   3. fman_pcd_muram_alloc(16) for source-TD; iomem via
+ *      fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram_handle, off) where
+ *      muram_handle = fman_get_muram(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd)).
+ *   4. fman_pcd_muram_alloc(num_members * 16) for members array.
+ *   5. memset_io both regions to zero (safe inactive state: source-TD
+ *      operationCode=0 means silicon walker never enters the chain).
+ *   6. iowrite32be FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE into source-TD type
+ *      field so body-2 can populate frg_pointer and the silicon
+ *      recognises this as a replicator entry point when body-2 stamps
+ *      the active OPCODE byte.
+ *   7. list_add_tail on pcd->replic_groups under pcd->lock so
+ *      fman_pcd_release() reaps leaked handles on driver unbind.
+ *
+ * Note: per-member FQID programming + NEXT chaining + NL_BIT stamping
+ * is deferred to body-2 (the encoder drop).  Body-1 leaves the members
+ * array all-zero - this is the same inactive-state safety invariant
+ * established by PR14d-body-1 (HMCT all-zero) and PR14e-body-1 (PLCR
+ * record all-zero): silicon cannot enter undefined state because the
+ * source-TD operationCode=0 short-circuits the walker.
  */
 struct fman_pcd_replic_group *
 fman_pcd_replic_group_create(struct fman_pcd *pcd,
-     const struct fman_pcd_replic_member *members,
-     u8 num_members)
+				     const struct fman_pcd_replic_member *members,
+				     u8 num_members)
 {
-if (!pcd || !members)
-return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
-if (num_members == 0 || num_members > FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_MAX_MEMBERS)
-return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
+	struct fman_pcd_replic_group *group;
+	struct muram_info *muram;
+	unsigned long off;
+	size_t members_sz;
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+	struct list_head *list;
 
-return ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP);
+	if (!pcd || !members)
+		return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
+	if (num_members == 0 || num_members > FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_MAX_MEMBERS)
+		return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
+
+	muram = fman_get_muram(fman_pcd_get_fman(pcd));
+	if (!muram)
+		return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
+
+	group = kzalloc(sizeof(*group), GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!group)
+		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
+
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&group->node);
+	spin_lock_init(&group->lock);
+	group->pcd = pcd;
+	group->num_members = num_members;
+
+	/* Source-TD: 16 B, 16-B aligned (gen_pool min_alloc_order=8 covers). */
+	off = fman_pcd_muram_alloc(pcd, FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+	if (IS_ERR_VALUE(off)) {
+		kfree(group);
+		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
+	}
+	group->source_td_off = off;
+	group->source_td = (void __iomem *)fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram, off);
+
+	/* Members array: num_members * 16 B contiguous. */
+	members_sz = (size_t)num_members * FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE;
+	off = fman_pcd_muram_alloc(pcd, members_sz);
+	if (IS_ERR_VALUE(off)) {
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, group->source_td_off,
+				    FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+		kfree(group);
+		return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
+	}
+	group->members_off = off;
+	group->members = (void __iomem *)fman_muram_offset_to_vbase(muram, off);
+	group->members_sz = members_sz;
+
+	/* Zero both regions before publishing - silicon walker treats
+	 * operationCode=0 as inactive, so this is the canonical safe state.
+	 */
+	memset_io(group->source_td, 0, FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+	memset_io(group->members, 0, members_sz);
+
+	/* Stamp the source-TD type field so body-2 can find it and the
+	 * silicon recognises the record as a replicator entry point once
+	 * body-2 writes the real operationCode.  type field is at offset 0,
+	 * holds FRM_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE in the high byte per RM 8.7.7.
+	 */
+	iowrite32be(FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SOURCE_TD_OPCODE << 24,
+		    group->source_td + FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_SRC_OFF_TYPE);
+
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(pcd);
+	list = fman_pcd_get_replic_list(pcd);
+	if (!pcd_lock || !list) {
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, group->members_off, members_sz);
+		fman_pcd_muram_free(pcd, group->source_td_off,
+				    FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+		kfree(group);
+		return ERR_PTR(-EINVAL);
+	}
+	mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+	list_add_tail(&group->node, list);
+	mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+
+	/* members[] is consumed by body-2 - body-1 stores the requested
+	 * FQIDs nowhere yet, on the principle that body-1 can land
+	 * independently of body-2 without leaving a partially-programmed
+	 * silicon state.  Pinning the FQIDs into the all-zero MURAM region
+	 * would defeat the inactive-state invariant.  Body-2's signature
+	 * will take (group, members[], num) and re-validate against
+	 * group->num_members.
+	 */
+	(void)members;
+
+	return group;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_replic_group_create);
 
 /**
  * fman_pcd_replic_group_destroy() - free one replicator group.
  *
- * PR14f-prep stub.  See <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h> for the full contract.
- * NULL-safe no-op until PR14f-body lands.
+ * Body-1 real destroy.  See <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h> for the contract.
+ * NULL-safe.  Acquires pcd->lock, list_del, frees MURAM (members first,
+ * then source-TD), frees handle.
+ *
+ * Body-3 will add a WARN_ON if any CC action template still references
+ * this group via FMAN_PCD_ACTION_REPLICATE - that requires a refcount
+ * field that gets bumped/dropped when add_key encodes the REPLICATE arm.
+ * For body-1 the assumption is single-consumer: only the test harness
+ * and the eventual ASK2 multicast flow type call this pair.
  */
 void fman_pcd_replic_group_destroy(struct fman_pcd_replic_group *group)
 {
-if (!group)
-return;
-/* PR14f-body: WARN if any CC action template still references this
- * group, free MURAM table, free handle.
- */
+	struct mutex *pcd_lock;
+
+	if (!group)
+		return;
+
+	pcd_lock = fman_pcd_get_lock(group->pcd);
+	if (pcd_lock) {
+		mutex_lock(pcd_lock);
+		list_del(&group->node);
+		mutex_unlock(pcd_lock);
+	} else {
+		/* PCD already torn down: leak the list anchor, it points at
+		 * freed memory anyway. */
+		WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
+	}
+
+	/* Zero before free so a future MURAM re-alloc that grabs the same
+	 * offset cannot inherit a half-active source-TD opcode.  Mirrors
+	 * PR14e-body-2's destroy enhancement.
+	 */
+	memset_io(group->members, 0, group->members_sz);
+	memset_io(group->source_td, 0, FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(group->pcd, group->members_off, group->members_sz);
+	fman_pcd_muram_free(group->pcd, group->source_td_off,
+			    FMAN_PCD_REPLIC_AD_SIZE);
+
+	kfree(group);
 }
-EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_replic_group_destroy);
\ No newline at end of file
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_replic_group_destroy);
